This paper focuses on the energy consumption of database servers and the optimization of query performance, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves profiling the energy distribution among server components and assessing energy consumption in relation to performance, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the study involves benchmarking and comparing different workloads, which falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR).
